  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: Metformin treatment normalises hormone values and metabolic parameters in women
      with PCOS. Ovulation is restored and bleeding periods become regular.

      Fifty women with PCOS (Rotterdam criteria) are randomised to either placebo or metformin for
      6 months. After a wash-out period of 3 months, the opposite treatment is given for another 6
      months. Measurements are performed before ech treatment period, every second month during
      treatment and after completing treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
